# Layout & Spacing

## App Shell: 16:9 Product Frame

The **entire** shell (sidebar + header + content) is drawn inside the **largest 16:9 rectangle** that fits the viewport.

| Layer | Classes / CSS |
|---|---|
| `.app-product-letterbox` | Centers shell; `min-height: 100vh/100dvh`; `overflow: hidden`; `background: #d4d4d4` |
| `.app-product-frame` | `position: relative`; `width: min(100vw, 100vh×16/9)`; `height: min(100vh, 100vw×9/16)`; column flex; `overflow: hidden` |
| Inner chrome | `flex h-full w-full min-h-0 overflow-hidden bg-white` → **Sidebar** + column |
| Main column | `flex min-h-0 min-w-0 flex-1 flex-col overflow-hidden` → **Header** + **`<main>`** |
| `<main>` | `flex min-h-0 flex-1 flex-col overflow-hidden bg-[#f5f9fe]` |
| `.shell-main-canvas` | `min-h-0 min-w-0 flex-1 overflow-y-auto`; CSS: `width: 100%; min-width: 0` — fills main column; single scroll for routed content (e.g. Home overview + charts scroll together) |

Non-16:9 viewports show letterboxing (gray bars). Sidebar nav uses `overflow-y-auto` on its inner stack; main uses `.shell-main-canvas` for route-content scrolling.

## Standard Page Container

Most in-shell pages follow this pattern:

```tsx
<div className="flex flex-col gap-4 md:gap-6 bg-white min-h-full px-[32px] pt-[12px] pb-[32px]">
```

**Exception:** Settings uses `pt-[20px]` instead of `pt-[12px]`.

## Page titles (L1 modules)

- Default: `h1` with `text-[32px] font-semibold text-[#101010]` inside the page’s vertical stack (`gap-4` / `md:gap-6` to the next block).
- **Do not** add a horizontal rule, `border-b`, or other separator **immediately under** the page title unless that module is **explicitly** spec’d with one — default is **no** title separator.

## Edge-to-Edge Separators

Full-width lines that escape horizontal padding:

```tsx
<div className="w-[calc(100%+64px)] h-[1px] bg-[#e0e0e0] mx-[-32px]" />
```

Reports uses `w-full h-[1px] bg-[#e0e0e0]` (no bleed) for its top-level dividers.

## Border Radius

| Element | Radius | Tailwind |
|---|---|---|
| Button | 8px | `rounded-[8px]` |
| Default | 8px | `rounded-lg` |
| Card | 12px | `rounded-[12px]` |
| Dashboard metric cards | 20px | `rounded-[20px]` |
| Dashboard chart surface top | 32px (top only) | `rounded-tl-[32px] rounded-tr-[32px]` |
| TextField | 4px | `rounded-[4px]` |
| Dropdown menu | 8px | `rounded-lg` |
| Full-round (avatar, pill) | 50% | `rounded-full` |
| Login hero image | 24px | `rounded-[24px]` |

## Shadows & Elevation

- Small: `shadow-elevation-sm` → `0 8px 16px rgba(16,16,16,0.07)` — cards, dropdowns
- Drawer: `shadow-[-4px_0_24px_rgba(0,0,0,0.08)]`
- Sticky footer: `shadow-[0_-2px_12px_rgba(16,16,16,0.06)]`

## Component Internal Padding

- Cards: `p-5` (20px) or `p-6` (24px) for consent/agreement
- Chart containers: `p-[24px]`
- Table cells: `px-6 py-4` (rows), `px-6 py-3` (headers)
- Modals/Popups: `px-8`
- Drawers: `px-8`
- Payment limit card: `p-6`

## Spacing Patterns

- Section gaps: `gap-4 md:gap-6`
- Card grid gaps: `gap-4` or `gap-6`
- Summary card strip: `gap-1` (4px) between cards + operator symbols
- Filter strip row: `gap-0` between segments (no border dividers)
- Dashboard surface section: `gap-4 md:gap-6 lg:gap-8`

## Scrollbar Styling

```
[&::-webkit-scrollbar]:w-2
[&::-webkit-scrollbar-track]:bg-transparent
[&::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb]:bg-gray-300
[&::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb]:rounded-full
[&::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb]:hover:bg-gray-400
```

## Interaction Patterns

Project-wide interaction guidance lives in **`interactions/interactions.mdc`**. Layout-adjacent defaults:

### Hover States
- Cards: opacity change (60% → 100%) or `hover:bg-[#f5f9fe]`
- Buttons: per emphasis level (see `buttons.mdc`)
- Links: underline appearance
- Dropdowns/rows: `hover:bg-[#f5f9fe]`

### Transitions
- Colors: `transition-colors`
- Shadows: `transition-shadow`
- Icon rotations: `transition-transform`
- Duration: default Tailwind timing (150–200ms)

### Click Outside Detection

```tsx
const ref = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);
useEffect(() => {
  const handler = (e: MouseEvent) => {
    if (ref.current && !ref.current.contains(e.target as Node)) setOpen(false);
  };
  document.addEventListener("mousedown", handler);
  return () => document.removeEventListener("mousedown", handler);
}, []);
```

## Responsive Design

- Mobile-first: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:` breakpoints
- Grid: `grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3`
- Flex direction: `flex-col sm:flex-row`
- Spacing: `gap-4 md:gap-6`
- Padding: `p-4 md:p-6 lg:p-8`

## Date & Time Formatting

- Date: "Today, 24 Jan" / "Yesterday, 23 Jan"
- Chart tooltip: full date "06 January 2026" (DD MMMM YYYY)
- Time: "7:30 AM, 23 Sep" / "8:00 AM Everyday"
- Use relative dates when appropriate

